pv_numeric.columns

In[]:
from scipy.stats import iqr

columns = pv_numeric.columns
IQR = {}
lower_threshold = {}
upper_threshold = {}

for col in columns:
    IQR[col] = iqr(pv_numeric[col])


    lower_threshold[col] = np.quantile(pv_numeric[col], 0.25) - 1.5 * IQR[col]
    upper_threshold[col] = np.quantile(pv_numeric[col], 0.75) + 1.5 * IQR[col]

print(f'IQR: {IQR}\n')
print(f'Lower thresholds: {lower_threshold}\n')
print(f'Upper thresholds: {upper_threshold}')

IQR: {'Payment': 1378.0, 'Lower_Estimate': 1042.0, 'Higher_Estimate': 1708.25, 'Denominator': 90.0}

Lower thresholds: {'Payment': 18794.0, 'Lower_Estimate': 17496.0, 'Higher_Estimate': 20274.375, 'Denominator': -21.0}

Upper thresholds: {'Payment': 24306.0, 'Lower_Estimate': 21664.0, 'Higher_Estimate': 27107.375, 'Denominator': 339.0}
In[]:
lower_thresholds = {'Payment': 18794.0, 'Lower_Estimate': 17496.0, 'Higher_Estimate': 20274.375,'Denominator': -21.0}
upper_thresholds = {'Payment': 24306.0, 'Lower_Estimate': 21664.0, 'Higher_Estimate': 27107.375,'Denominator': 339.0}

#Removing outliers based on the thresholds
for column in lower_thresholds:
    df = pv_numeric[(pv_numeric[column] >= lower_thresholds[column]) & (pv_numeric[column] <= upper_thresholds[column])]

#Displaying the DataFrame after removing outliers

from scipy.stats import iqr

columns = pv_numeric.columns
IQR = {}
lower_threshold = {}
upper_threshold = {}

for col in columns:
    IQR[col] = iqr(pv_numeric[col])


    lower_threshold[col] = np.quantile(pv_numeric[col], 0.25) - 1.5 * IQR[col]
    upper_threshold[col] = np.quantile(pv_numeric[col], 0.75) + 1.5 * IQR[col]

print(f'IQR: {IQR}\n')
print(f'Lower thresholds: {lower_threshold}\n')
print(f'Upper thresholds: {upper_threshold}')

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Step 1: Remove outliers using the IQR method
Q1 = df['Payment'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['Payment'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

# Filter the dataframe to remove the outliers
df_no_outliers_iqr = df[(df['Payment'] >= lower_bound) & (df['Payment'] <= upper_bound)]

# Step 2: Visualize boxplot before and after outlier removal

# Boxplot before removing outliers
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.boxplot(x=df['Payment'])
plt.title('Boxplot Before Removing Outliers')
plt.show()

# Boxplot after removing outliers (using IQR method)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.boxplot(x=df_no_outliers_iqr['Payment'])
plt.title('Boxplot After Removing Outliers')
plt.show()

Q1 = df['Denominator'].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df['Denominator'].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

# Print the bounds to debug
print("Lower Bound:", lower_bound)
print("Upper Bound:", upper_bound)

# Filter the dataframe to remove the outliers
df_no_outliers_iqr = df[(df['Denominator'] >= lower_bound) & (df['Denominator'] <= upper_bound)]

# Check the size of the dataframe before and after removing outliers
print(f"Original DataFrame Size: {df.shape}")
print(f"Filtered DataFrame Size: {df_no_outliers_iqr.shape}")

# Step 2: Visualize boxplot before and after outlier removal

# Boxplot before removing outliers
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.boxplot(x=df['Denominator'])
plt.title('Boxplot Before Removing Outliers')
plt.show()

# Boxplot after removing outliers (using IQR method)
if df_no_outliers_iqr.shape[0] > 0:  # Check if there are data points left
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=df_no_outliers_iqr['Denominator'])
    plt.title('Boxplot After Removing Outliers')
    plt.show()
else:
    print("No data left after removing outliers.")

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Assuming 'merged_df' is your DataFrame
# Select only numeric columns from the DataFrame
numeric_columns = ['Payment', 'Lower_Estimate', 'Higher_Estimate', 'Denominator']

# Group by 'State' and sum up the values of the numeric columns
state_comparison = merged_df.groupby('State')[numeric_columns].sum().reset_index()

# Create a figure and axis
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))

# Set the positions of the bars on the x-axis
bar_width = 0.2
index = range(len(state_comparison))

# Plot each numeric column as a bar
colors = sns.color_palette("Set2", len(numeric_columns))  # Using Seaborn color palette for different colors
for i, column in enumerate(numeric_columns):
    plt.bar(
        [x + i * bar_width for x in index],  # Shift bars for each column
        state_comparison[column],
        bar_width,
        label=column,
        color=colors[i]
    )

# Set labels, title, and legend
plt.xlabel('State')
plt.ylabel('Total Value')
plt.title('Comparative Total Values of Numeric Columns by State')
plt.xticks([x + bar_width * (len(numeric_columns) / 2 - 0.5) for x in index], state_comparison['State'], rotation=45)

# Add a legend to distinguish the columns
plt.legend()

# Adjust the layout for better spacing
plt.tight_layout()

# Display the plot
plt.show()

import pandas as pd

axs[1].set_ylabel('Average Higher Estimate')

axs[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

axs[2].set_xlabel('Payment Measure ID')
axs[2].set_ylabel('Average Denominator')
axs[2].set_title('Average Denominator by Payment Measure ID')
